description: Treat dot-prefixed image files as hidden (ignored in galleries and git)
alwaysApply: true
---

# Hidden Dot-Prefixed Images

Convention:

- Any media file whose name starts with `.` (for example `.IMG_1234.jpg`) is considered hidden.

Gallery behavior:

- Shortcodes and templates that render images must skip files whose names start with `.`.

Git behavior:

- Do not commit dot-prefixed media files.
- Root `.gitignore` includes `static/images/**/.*` so these are ignored automatically.

When adding or renaming pictures:

- Use a leading `.` to hide a file from galleries without deleting it.
- Do not reference dot-prefixed files from content.
